        <!-- Section 1: Project Overview (Expanded) -->
        <section class="card rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 mb-10">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 border-b border-primary-violet pb-2">What Fermah is Building: Solving the ZK Bottleneck</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                Fermah is building a decentralized, two-sided **marketplace** designed to solve the complexity and high cost associated with generating **Zero-Knowledge Proofs (ZKPs)**. While ZKPs are essential for the scalability and privacy of all modern blockchain applications (ZK rollups, zkEVMs, and ZK bridges), the current ecosystem faces severe bottlenecks:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 text-gray-400 mt-4 space-y-2">
                <li>**High Hardware Cost:** Proof generation demands massive computational power, primarily from specialized, expensive hardware (high-end GPUs, ASICs).</li>
                <li>**Orchestration Complexity:** Projects must maintain complex, localized infrastructure to queue and manage proving jobs, leading to centralized points of failure.</li>
                <li>**Inconsistent Speed:** Latency varies wildly based on available resources and proof complexity, impacting dApp user experience.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
                Fermah's mission is to abstract away this infrastructure complexity, providing a **Universal Proof Generation Layer** that makes ZKPs **cheap, fast, and reliably accessible** for any developer. Critically, Fermah ensures **credible neutrality** by being architected to support *all* major proof systems—including zkVMs, zkEVMs, Groth16, PLONK, and STARKs—making it the end-game infrastructure for ZK computation.
            </p>
        </section>

