            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center gradient-text">The Proof Generation Marketplace</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-stretch">

                <!-- Card 1: Seekers (Demand Side) -->
                <div class="card rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
                    <svg class="w-12 h-12 mb-4 text-primary-violet" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path></svg>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-white hover:text-primary-violet transition duration-300">Seekers (Demand)</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400">
                        These are the users and projects (ZK rollups, DeFi protocols, privacy apps) that **request** proofs. They submit the computation they need verified without having to worry about the underlying hardware or proving process.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 2: The Matchmaker (Orchestration) -->
                <div class="card rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col items-center text-center border-2 border-primary-violet">
                    <svg class="w-12 h-12 mb-4 text-primary-violet" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 7v10c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4V7M4 7c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4M4 7c0-2.21 3.582-4 8-4s8 1.79 8 4m0 5c0 2.21-3.582 4-8 4s-8-1.79-8-4"></path></svg>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-white hover:text-primary-violet transition duration-300">Matchmaker (Orchestrator)</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400">
                        The core routing layer that intelligently connects Seekers' proof requests to the most optimal **Prover Node** based on speed, cost, and machine capability. It ensures efficient resource allocation across the network.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 3: Prover Nodes (Supply Side) -->
                <div class="card rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
                    <svg class="w-12 h-12 mb-4 text-primary-violet" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 12a9 9 0 01-9 9m9-9a9 9 0 00-9-9m9 9h-3a8 8 0 01-8-8v4a3 3 0 00-3 3v1a3 3 0 003 3h4m-4-7a3 3 0 013-3h1m-1 7a3 3 0 003-3v-1a3 3 0 00-3-3m-1 14h2"></path></svg>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-white hover:text-primary-violet transition duration-300">Prover Nodes (Supply)</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-400">
                        The decentralized infrastructure providers who offer computational power (GPUs, FPGAs) to generate the proofs. Initially bootstrapped by **EigenLayer Operators** for enhanced security.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- New Section 4: Economic Model and Native Token -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center text-gray-200">The Fermah Economic Model ($\text{FERM}$)</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <!-- Card 1: Economic Structure -->
                <div class="card rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-primary-violet hover:text-white transition duration-300">Incentive Alignment</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                        Fermah operates on a two-sided market model powered by a native token ($\text{FERM}$), designed to align incentives, guarantee proof quality, and ensure the network is sufficiently decentralized and capitalized.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-3 text-accent-green font-bold text-xl">💰</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong class="text-white">Seeker Payments:</strong> Seekers pay fees (in $\text{ETH}$ or stablecoins) for proof generation. This demand-side revenue is primarily distributed to Prover Nodes.
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-3 text-accent-green font-bold text-xl">🎁</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong class="text-white">Prover Rewards:</strong> Prover Nodes receive fees for computational work, plus block rewards in $\text{FERM}$ for their service and staking security.
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 2: FERM Utility -->
                <div class="card rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-primary-violet hover:text-white transition duration-300">Native Token Utility ($\text{FERM}$)</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
                        The $\text{FERM}$ token is the cornerstone of the network's decentralized governance and security layer.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-3 text-primary-violet font-bold text-xl">🏛️</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong class="text-white">Governance:</strong> $\text{FERM}$ holders participate in governance decisions, voting on protocol upgrades, fee structures, and resource allocation.
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-3 text-primary-violet font-bold text-xl">🔒</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong class="text-white">Staking & Slashing:</strong> Provers must stake $\text{FERM}$ (or re-stake $\text{ETH}$ via EigenLayer) to participate. This stake is subject to slashing if a node acts maliciously or fails to complete jobs reliably.
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-3 text-primary-violet font-bold text-xl">🔥</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong class="text-white">Fee Discount & Burning:</strong> Using $\text{FERM}$ for proof payments grants fee discounts, and a portion of all network fees is proposed to be periodically burned to maintain deflationary pressure.
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>


